RIFT VALLEY FEVER - NIGER (05): (TAHOUA)
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 17 Nov 2016
Source: Gistmaster [edited]
https://www.niyitabiti.net/2016/11/rift-valley-fever-kills-32-in-niger/


At least 32 people have died since late August [2016] in an epidemic of Rift Valley fever in the western Niger region of Tahoua, the country's health ministry said [Thu 17 Nov 2016].

A ministry statement read on national radio said 230 people had been infected with the fever-causing viral disease that mainly affects animals but also humans, "unfortunately including 32 deaths."

The mortality rate had fallen from 50 percent 3 months ago to 14 percent due to a government information campaign urging people to bury animal carcasses and handle contaminated animals with care and avoid drinking raw milk.

Symptoms include fever, headaches, and stomach pain in people, while in livestock, common symptoms are fever and bleeding.

